    "encrypted": "false",
    "instructions_important": "false",
    "long_instructions": "### The Random Block \r\nThe `random` block lets your code pick a random option every time it runs. This means your music can sound a little different each time!\r\n\r\n- You can put loops inside the random block—just like you would under `when run`.\r\n-  Everything inside that loop will run normally, but only one of the random choices will be picked each time!\r\n\r\n**Do This:** \r\n- Add your own sounds into each `play together` block in the start code. \r\n- Change the number of times you want each to repeat. \r\n- Press \"Run\" at least three times to see how the `random` block works. ",
